notes:
Implemented backend data model + resolution (src-tauri/src/settings.rs, new). NOT closing/committing per orchestrator.

STORAGE: reuses the existing M0 key/value 'settings' table (no migration added). All agent config lives under ONE key: 'agent_settings' (JSON). Defaults live in CODE (AgentSettings::default), never seeded rows -> zero-config works with no row present (FR-7.4). get_settings merges a stored blob over defaults via FIELD-LEVEL serde defaults (#[serde(default=..)] per field + Default impls), so a partial/older blob still fills missing fields from code. JSON is camelCase, matching PRD §5.5: adapters{command,args,cwd}, defaultAdapter, models{followUp,artifactUpdate,inAppAsk}, plus timeoutSecs (u64 SECONDS, default 900=15min FR-5.3) and agentBinaryPath (Option<String>, null/empty=no override, FR-7.3). update_settings validates default_adapter names an existing adapter before writing; write is a single atomic upsert (N4-safe).

RESOLUTION API for b12.2 (spawner) — two calls, in order:
  let s = settings::get_settings(&conn)?;
  let inv: ResolvedInvocation = s.resolve(Purpose::{FollowUp|ArtifactUpdate|InAppAsk}, project_root: &Path, prompt: &str)?; // {program,args,cwd}
  let program: PathBuf = settings::resolve_agent_binary(&inv.program, s.agent_binary_path.as_deref())?;
  Command::new(program).args(&inv.args).current_dir(&inv.cwd); timeout = Duration::from_secs(s.timeout_secs);
resolve() is PURE (no I/O, only errors UnknownAdapter). resolve_agent_binary is the ONLY effectful fn: override wins; else absolute command returned as-is; else cached login-shell 'zsh -lc which <cmd>' (BINARY_CACHE OnceLock, keyed by command). Non-abs/not-found -> SettingsError::BinaryNotFound. Only the (trusted, local) command name ever touches a shell (single-quoted); prompt/args NEVER do.

SUBSTITUTION SAFETY: expand() is single-pass over the TEMPLATE, whole-string per-arg, never shell-interpreted. Values inserted verbatim, scanner continues in template (not the value) so a prompt containing literal {model}/{project_root} is NOT re-substituted (classic sequential-replace injection avoided). One template string -> exactly one argv element; no whitespace splitting. Tested with spaces/quotes/braces/newlines/backticks/$()/;|.

COMMANDS (appended at END of commands.rs): get_agent_settings(db) -> AgentSettings; set_agent_settings(app, db, settings) -> () emits 'settings-changed' event. Registered in lib.rs generate_handler!. For 959.4 UI: invoke('get_agent_settings'); invoke('set_agent_settings', { settings: {...camelCase...} }) (rename_all=snake_case; DTO is AgentSettings itself, lives in settings.rs not types crate — CLI doesn't need it). Listen for 'settings-changed'.

DEAD_CODE: module has #![allow(dead_code)] because the resolve/binary seam has no in-crate caller until b12.2 (app lib is a cdylib -> unused pub items flagged). Every item is unit-tested. DROP the allow when b12.2 wires the spawner.

